G.L. c. 186, \u00a7 14.proposition: Under G.L. c. 186, § 14, every residential lease in Massachusetts contains an implied covenant of quiet enjoyment, protecting tenants from substantial interference with their use and enjoyment of the premises.

G.L. c. 218, \u00a7 19.proposition: This Court has jurisdiction over this action pursuant to G.L. c. 218, § 19 and G.L. c. 223, § 2, as the property at issue is located in Somerville, Massachusetts.

G.L. c. 223, \u00a7 2.proposition: This Court has jurisdiction over this action pursuant to G.L. c. 218, § 19 and G.L. c. 223, § 2, as the property at issue is located in Somerville, Massachusetts.

G.L. c. 223, \u00a7 6.proposition: Venue is proper in Somerville District Court pursuant to G.L. c. 223, § 6, because the leased premises and the Defendant’s business activities are located within this judicial district.
